tldr: The user requested an evaluation of the codebase for a sleep questionnaire
  application to implement a database and an admin dashboard. A plan was created
  to add a database for responses, a simple password-protected admin dashboard
  with CSV export, and update the demographics collected. The initial steps of
  updating the demographics and the Prisma schema have been completed.
overview: The user initiated a task to enhance a sleep questionnaire application
  by integrating a database for response storage and developing a
  client-accessible admin dashboard. After evaluating the existing codebase,
  which already featured a comprehensive questionnaire and PDF generation, it
  was determined that database implementation, data retrieval (CSV export), and
  an authentication-protected admin dashboard were the primary missing
  components. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for
  the database, implementing a simple password-based authentication system via
  environment variables, and updating the demographic data collected to include
  year of birth and sex while retaining existing fields. The plan outlines the
  creation of new API routes for saving and retrieving responses, a login/logout
  system, and an admin dashboard to view and export data. So far, the
  demographics in the types, validations, and form components have been updated,
  and the  model has been added to the Prisma schema.
